<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="365" pageId="2" pageNumber="364" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,389,1888,1946]" box="[151,389,1888,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,389,1888,1914]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="364" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,389,1888,1914]" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,316,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
<taxonomicName box="[151,276,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xenovarta</taxonomicName>
lui
</emphasis>
sp. n.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,389,1888,1946]" box="[151,350,1922,1946]" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
(Plate I, 
<figureCitation box="[246,338,1922,1946]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
Figure 
<number box="[326,338,1922,1946]" pageId="2" pageNumber="364" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,402,1994,2018]" box="[151,402,1994,2018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="364">
Length. Male: 
<quantity box="[316,398,1994,2018]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="364" unit="mm" value="8.3">8.3mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Dark bluish green with orange stripes (Plate I: A &amp; B). Vertex, pronotum and scutellum with orange longitudinal stripes, two small black spots on either side of median line near apex of vertex, lateral area traversed by stripe continuing on pronotum and scutellum then on to clavus as median pair, pronotum with additional lateral stripe continuing on clavus as lateral stripe (Plate I: C). Median area of frontoclypeus, basal areas of clypellus and lora yellow (Plate I: D). Forewing dark bluish green except brown apex (Plate I: A &amp; B). Ventral area of thorax, abdomen, and leg ochraceous.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Vertex acutely triangularly produced in front of eyes, about 
<number box="[879,914,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.5">2.5</number>
x as long as interocular width, 
<number box="[1266,1301,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.6">1.6</number>
x as long as pronotum (Plate I: C), lateral margins sharp, carinate (Plate I: B). Face longer than wide, frontoclypeus elongate and narrow, clypellus wider near apex than at base, not extending beyond genal curve (Plate I: D). Pronotum about 
<date box="[151,179,476,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
<number box="[151,165,476,500]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
as wide as long, longer than vertex (Plate I: C). Scutellum slightly shorter than pronotum (Plate I: C). Forewing with four apical and two anteapical cells, inner anteapical cell open behind (Plate I: E). Male segment X weakly sclerotized, long, with one strongly sclerotized and apically bifid process (Plate I: F &amp; G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,583,608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side elongate, base wide, apex narrow, middle of dorsal margin and ventral margin strongly inflexed, with sclerotised area, apex with subtriangular membranous lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1212,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[1201,1212,620,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Valve fused to subgenital plates the latter with uniseriate row of macrosetae, with pair of sclerotized lobes dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1334,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[1323,1334,655,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Style with lobe in middle, subapical lobe discernable but not well developed, apophysis distally rugulose (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1398,692,716]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[1387,1398,692,716]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Connective narrowly linear, stem half as long as arms, quadrate, arms in contact with each other (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1396,727,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1396,727,751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Aedeagus apex narrow, with pair of subapical processes, gonopore large, apical (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1122,764,788]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,249,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,579,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1398,566,1738]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xenovarta lui sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="365">
Figs 
<number box="[1111,1122,764,788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[1156,1167,764,788]" pageId="3" pageNumber="365" value="1.0">1</number>
F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
